Using inspiration from other WAGO holders and strain reliefs, we created our own 3D-printable WAGO 221 side-by-side holders. The connectors snap right into place and have spaces for zip ties to be held in to remove strain from the wires. We recommend using these for CAN and any other small gauge wires on your robot. There are different parts of the model to indicate the green and yellow connections if you can print in multiple materials.

We created a custom cover for our mk4i swerve modules this year that uses built-in versions of our WAGO holders to make all of the CAN connections and the power connection for motors and the CAN-coder easily serviceable. The covers also contain any grease you have in the gears and prevent any foreign objects from getting in. There are two versions we have available for printing, one with a cover for the cables and the top, and one without.

We would also like to share the Onshape files for out robot this year. Feel free to check them out!

If you have any comments or questions, I’d be happy to answer.
